<font FACE="Arial Black" SIZE="7" COLOR="#000000">

<p align="center"></font><font FACE="Arial Black" COLOR="#000000" size="6">The Actor Model</font></p>

<p>&nbsp;<font FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="7" COLOR="#000000">

<ul>
  <li><font FACE="Times New Roman" COLOR="#000000" size="6">The universe contains computation agents, called actors</font></li>
  <li><font FACE="Times New Roman" COLOR="#000000" size="6">Actors perform computation through asynchronous, point-to-point message passing</font></li>
  <li><font FACE="Times New Roman" COLOR="#000000" size="6">Each actor is defined by its state, a mail queue to external messages and internal behavior</font></li>
  <li><font FACE="Times New Roman" COLOR="#000000" size="6">State is defined by internal data (acquaintances)</font></li>
  <li><font FACE="Times New Roman" COLOR="#000000" size="6">An actor reacts to the external environment by executing its procedure skills (scripts) 
</font></li>
</ul>
</font>
